<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-8986] Server$Call object is never released after it is sent</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-8986</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When an IPC response cannot be returned without blocking an Server$Call object is attached to the SelectionKey of the write selector.  However the call object is never removed from the SlectionKey. So for a connection that rarely has large responses but is long lived there is a lot of data.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12613722">HADOOP-8986</key>
            <summary>Server$Call object is never released after it is sent</summary>
